David MacMichael is a former CIA analyst who exposed the 1984 State Department White Paper on Central America. He is Senior Fellow of the Council on Hemispheric Affairs and is the editor of Unclassified, the newsletter of the Association of National Security Alumni. Several issues are discussed, such as CIA drug running in South East Asia and Central America, the Christic Institute case, and the INSLAW matter.

